Class SimpleRenderer

java.lang.Object
  org.semanticweb.owlapi.util.SimpleRenderer
All Implemented Interfaces:
OWLObjectRenderer, OWLAnnotationAxiomVisitor, OWLAnnotationObjectVisitor, OWLAnnotationValueVisitor, OWLAxiomVisitor, OWLClassExpressionVisitor, OWLDataRangeVisitor, OWLDataVisitor, OWLEntityVisitor, OWLIndividualVisitor, OWLObjectVisitor, OWLPropertyExpressionVisitor, SWRLObjectVisitor
public class SimpleRenderer
extends java.lang.Object
implements OWLObjectVisitor, OWLObjectRenderer

Author: Matthew Horridge
The University Of Manchester
Bio-Health Informatics Group
Date: 26-Nov-2006

A simple renderer that can be used for debugging purposes and provide an implementation of the toString method for different implementations.

setPrefixesFromOntologyFormat

public void setPrefixesFromOntologyFormat(OWLOntology ontology,
                                          OWLOntologyManager manager,
                                          boolean processImportedOntologies)
Resets the short form provider and adds prefix name to prefix mappings based on the specified ontology's format (if it is a prefix format) and possibly the ontologies in the imports closure.

Parameters:
ontology - The ontology whose format will be used to obtain prefix mappings
manager - A manager which can be used to obtain the format of the specified ontology (and possibly ontologies in its imports closure)
processImportedOntologies - Specifies whether or not the prefix mapping should be obtained from imported ontologies.

setPrefix

public void setPrefix(java.lang.String prefixName,
                      java.lang.String prefix)
Sets a prefix name for a given prefix. Note that prefix names MUST end with a colon.

Parameters:
prefixName - The prefix name (ending with a colon)
prefix - The prefix that the prefix name maps to
